        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=58064&amp;TOPIC_ID=6835&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Terrorclaws+or+shawl+quest%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         There a HUGE difference in mana use when soloing and raiding.</P><P>While there as many solo fights that we use hardly any mana to dark, fear, and re-dot.</P><P>When it comes to raiding, its all about mana effeciency.</P><P>Hps don't mean anything on raids, cause by time u done being buffed, the difference between 3800 and 4200 really won't matter at all. If we get summoned or end up on rampage, its FD, HS, or a fast healer that will save us not a few hundred hps.</P><P>So any chance you get to pick up extended affliction 3, affliction effciency 3, affliction haste 3, take them over any other item. In my opinion of course. </P><P>The cumualtive mana savings of these 3 items together, stacked with SCM3, and alteration specialzation is staggering in long fights. Add any FT items on top of these, and it helps a ton. </P><P>Its easy to run out of mana on big fights like CT RoS etc. where you are constantly casting vexing, funeral, splurting, degen, succesion, healing with shadowbond and pact of shadow, and repeating as neccessary with little chance to med. When u can deal out massive damage and help out with heals in between, then others see the flexibility of our class and our value on raids. So the more efficient we are with our mana on raids the more we can contribute to the guild.</P><P>So always be thinking of whats best for me when soloing, AND whats best for me as a raid memeber when you looking at gear. If you plan to be a raiding alot, then give up hps for items with focus, and hope VI puts nice focus on hps items for us later :)</P><P>So to answer your question, I would use terrorclaw until you can complete the shawl(start working on it asap I would suggest) and swap them out first chance you get. FT2 and 50hps 50mana 8 to the other stats/resists blows terror away.</P><P><BR>Cuku (Fire & Fury)<BR>Iksar Warlock (FV Server)</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223029" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223029</a> </P><P></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
