        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Shawl quest looks easy on paper until you try to do it. IT IS A PAIN... I spent 3 days, 6 hours a day in EW camping snow griff eggs.. only to fail on final combine (and the combine was trivial)... let alone gathering silk, wurm biles, upping boring-ass trade skills.. plus, to get number 8 you gotta have 2-3 groups ready and able to help you wander IC, kill 4-8 giants at once, while keeping a light blue dorf alive... for necros the shawl is crap.. well, 8th shawl has nice stats (+50hp and the effect, int)</P><P> I'd go ODS.. it saves you a LOT of mana in the end.. even if it saves you 20 mana per cast that still kicks the hell out of any flowing thought items you could get. On average ODS added at least 1 ToN on a bar of mana (405 mana)... and ODS gives like 10 or 12hp from stamina if I remember. IMO this beats the Terrorclaw hide.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34033" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34033</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
